<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased Launch Latencies>
Between 12:32 PM PDT and 2:40 PM PDT, we experienced elevated launch times for EC2 instance managed by Auto Scaling in the US-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Error Rates>
We continue to investigate increased error rates for newly created VPC functions in the US-WEST-2 Region. This includes VPC functions created via the console as well as those created via the API or CLI. The issue has been resolved for non-VPC functions.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased API Error Rates>
Between 12:47 PM PDT and 4:55 PM PDT, we experienced increased error rates for newly created functions in US-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased Provisioning Latencies>
We are seeing an improvement in the increased provisioning times affecting load balancers in the US-WEST-2 Region. We continue to work towards full recovery.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased Provisioning Latencies>
Between 1:00 PM and 4:48 PM PDT, we experienced increased provisioning times for load balancers in the US-WEST-2 Region. Connectivity to load balancers was not affected. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Delays in starting clusters>
We continue to investigate delays in starting clusters in the US-WEST-2 Region. Existing clusters are not affected.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Delays in starting clusters>
Between 1:10 PM and 4:20 PM PDT we experienced delays in starting clusters in US-West-2 Region. Existing clusters were not affected. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Delays in starting clusters>
Between 1:10 PM and 4:20 PM PDT we experienced delays in starting clusters in US-WEST-2 Region. Existing clusters were not affected. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased API Errors>
We're investigating increased error rates and latencies for the EC2 APIs in the US-WEST-2 Region.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Increased API Errors>
Between 8:48 PM and 9:25 PM PDT we experienced increased error rates and latencies in the US-WEST-2 Region. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.
